## Decisions Made
- Guard placement at pipeline_insert() function level rather than CLI dispatch: ensures both direct CLI calls and any internal function calls are caught, with _changeset-apply bypass via internal flag variable
- Two-layer defense (runtime CLI guard + skill doc reinforcement): runtime guard is the hard blocker, skill doc changes reduce the chance sub-agents attempt the call in the first place
- extract-candidates 4d derivability: strengthened with mandatory code reading requirement (external change accepted as intentional)

## Problems Encountered
- Sub-agents during batch-refine (#18492, #18479) called _pipeline-insert directly instead of returning candidates to orchestrator for changeset file writing: resolved by adding branch-aware guard that blocks execution on knowledge/batch-* branches

## Constraints Identified
- _pipeline-insert must remain callable from _changeset-apply on main after Report PR merge: bypass flag _KD_VIA_CHANGESET_APPLY used to allow the legitimate code path
- Pipe subshell inheritance: _KD_VIA_CHANGESET_APPLY set as parent variable before pipe so subshell inherits it in changeset_apply()

